

---
const pageTitle = "Ego";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{pageTitle}</title>
    <style>
      :root {
        --paper: #ffffff;
        --ink: #000000;
        --line: #000000;
        --soft: #efefef;
        --blue: #0000ee;
        --red: #cc0000;
        --green: #008000;
      }

      html, body {
        margin: 0;
        padding: 0;
        background: var(--paper);
        color: var(--ink);
        font-family: "Times New Roman", Times, serif;
        font-size: 18px;
        line-height: 1.55;
      }

      a { text-decoration: underline; }
      a.blue { color: var(--blue); }
      a.red { color: var(--red); }
      a.green { color: var(--green); }

      .page {
        width: min(900px, calc(100% - 48px));
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 28px 0 60px;
      }

      .topbar {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 10px 14px;
        margin-bottom: 18px;
        text-align: center;
        background: #fafafa;
      }

      .frame {
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 22px 24px 28px;
      }

      h1 {
        font-size: 40px;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 0 0 8px;
      }

      .subtitle {
        text-align: center;
        font-size: 16px;
        margin-bottom: 24px;
      }

      .divider {
        text-align: center;
        margin: 18px 0 24px;
      }

      p { margin-bottom: 16px; }

      .quote {
        margin: 22px auto;
        max-width: 680px;
        border: 1px solid var(--line);
        padding: 14px;
        background: var(--soft);
        font-style: italic;
        text-align: center;
      }

      .section-title {
        font-size: 28px;
        text-align: center;
        margin: 34px 0 16px;
      }

      .mini-links {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 30px;
      }

      .mini-links a {
        margin: 0 10px;
      }

      .footer-note {
        text-align: center;
        margin-top: 26px;
        font-size: 14px;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="page">
      <div class="topbar">
        [ <a class="blue" href="/">home</a> ]
        [ <a class="red" href="/foundations">foundations</a> ]
        [ <a class="green" href="/foundations/what-is-the-self">self</a> ]
        [ <a class="blue" href="/foundations/persona">next</a> ]
      </div>

      <main class="frame">
        <h1>Ego</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">foundations / identity / archive entry</p>

        <div class="divider">***</div>

        <p>
          The ego is the part of you that says “I”.
        </p>

        <p>
          It is your sense of identity, your awareness of being a separate individual.
        </p>

        <div class="quote">
          The ego is not the whole self. It is only the center of consciousness.
        </div>

        <h2 class="section-title">what the ego does</h2>

        <p>
          The ego organizes your experience. It allows you to think, decide, remember, and act in the world.
        </p>

        <p>
          Without it, there would be no stable sense of direction or identity.
        </p>

        <h2 class="section-title">the limitation</h2>

        <p>
          The ego believes it is the whole of you.
        </p>

        <p>
          But it only knows what is conscious. Everything outside of that lies in the <a class="blue" href="/foundations/conscious-and-unconscious">unconscious</a>.
        </p>

        <div class="quote">
          When the ego takes itself as the whole, it becomes blind.
        </div>

        <h2 class="section-title">ego inflation</h2>

        <p>
          When the ego identifies too strongly with power, knowledge, or identity, it becomes inflated.
        </p>

        <p>
          This leads to arrogance, rigidity, and a loss of balance.
        </p>

        <p>
          Life often corrects this through failure, confusion, or collapse.
        </p>

        <h2 class="section-title">ego and growth</h2>

        <p>
          The goal is not to destroy the ego.
        </p>

        <p>
          The goal is to place it in proper relationship to the <a class="green" href="/foundations/what-is-the-self">self</a>.
        </p>

        <p>
          A healthy ego is flexible. It can change, learn, and recognize its limits.
        </p>

        <div class="mini-links">
          <a class="blue" href="/foundations">back to foundations index</a>
          <a class="blue" href="/foundations/persona">continue to: persona</a>
          <a class="red" href="/foundations/conscious-and-unconscious">conscious + unconscious</a>
          <a class="green" href="/dreams/shadow-projection">shadow</a>
        </div>

        <p class="footer-note">the ego is a tool. not the ruler.</p>
      </main>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>